				<div class="posttitle">
					<h2><a href="http://www.twilightuniverse.com/?p=363" rel="bookmark" title="iPhone">iPhone</a></h2>
					<span class="postmeta">Monday, July 2nd, 2007 | <a href="http://www.twilightuniverse.com/?cat=1" title="View all posts in blog" rel="category">blog</a> |  <a href="http://www.twilightuniverse.com" title="Visit Gregory&#8217;s website" rel="external">Gregory</a> </span>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="postcontent"><p>So&#8230; Yeah. I admit it, I&#8217;m weak.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ve wanted an iPhone for months now, something about the UI just clicked with me, and I needed to get a new phone anyhow&#8230; so I caved and bought one on Saturday at the SF Apple Store.</p>
<p>I pity the suckers who lined up Friday though, as it was really easy to get one (though they were flying off the shelves) and I was in and out in a couple of minutes. Activation went smoothly and the newer version of EDGE* that AT&amp;T rolled out Friday for data transfer is almost as fast as WiFi &#8211; so all that hot air that was written about it being slow is just that &#8211; bunk.</p>
<p>So very pretty, and really nice to use&#8230; top marks.</p>
<p>I&#8217;ll write up a proper review soon and post with photos, but suffice to say: so far, so worth it.</p>
<p><small>*despite what you may have heard EGDE is technically a 3G network, not 2G.</small></p>
</div>
